-- Orascom Telecom Required to Pay Lacom Unit Debt to Algeria, Khabar Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2010-11-03T07:44:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/orascom-telecom-required-to-pay-lacom-unit-debt-to-algeria-khabar-reports.html
Orascom Telecom Holding SAE is
required to pay debt owed by its unit Lacom to the Algerian
state,  El Khabar  reported, citing Communications Minister  Moussa Benhamadi .  Benhamadi also said that the Algerian government still
hasn’t decided on the legal framework for acquiring Orascom
Telecom’s mobile phone unit Djezzy, according to the Algiers-
based newspaper.  Lacom’s debts include 30 million Algerian dinars ($407,996)
owed to the regulatory authority, El Khabar cited Benhamadi as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at   ogalal@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net . 